Japan Tops Mexico to Reach Women’s World Cup Quarterfinals; England Wins

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-07-01T18:17:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-01/japan-beats-mexico-to-secure-women-s-world-cup-quartefinal-spot.html
Japan  defeated Mexico 4-0 to qualify
for the quarterfinals at soccer’s Women’s World Cup in Germany,
while England came from behind to beat New Zealand 2-1.  Homare Sawa scored three goals and Shinobou Ohon added one
in Leverkusen for Japan, which is guaranteed of finishing among
the first two teams in Group B. The 16-team field is split into
four groups with the top two in each progressing to the
quarterfinals.  Jill Scott and Jessica Clark scored second-half goals to
lift England past New Zealand, which got an 18th-minute goal
from Sarah Gregorius in Dresden.  Japan leads the group with six points, England has four
points, Mexico has one point and  New Zealand  none. England plays
Japan and New Zealand faces Mexico in the final group games on
July 5.  In Group C games tomorrow, North Korea plays Sweden in
Augsburg and the U.S. meets Colombia in Sinsheim.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 